author: sunderme
message:
fix cursor position in undo with completer (and placeholders)

completing a command which has at least one placholder and putting text
into that placeholder, leads to wong cursor position after undoing all
completer steps.
Example is \frac{sdasd}{den} , starting with the completer after \fra
and doing undo until \fra appears again.

second time ... after all files were closed the first time. Now saving
is enforced to happen only once.

author: MeanSquaredError
message:
Fix events processing in tests (#1055)

* Only define SyntaxCheck::waitForQueueProcess when tests are enabled. Add a description to that method explaining why it can be used only in self-tests context.

* Move the code that processes events during a test run into a separate function and add a call for processing deferred delete events.

* Process all events (including deferred events) in SyntaxCheck::waitForQueueProcess.

* Clean up source code whitespace

* Install a native event filter that discards all native events while the tests are running.

message:
chore: Set permissions for GitHub actions (#2329)

Restrict the GitHub token permissions only to the required ones; this way, even if the attackers will succeed in compromising your workflow, they won’t be able to do much.

- Included permissions for the action. https://github.com/ossf/scorecard/blob/main/docs/checks.md#token-permissions

https://docs.github.com/en/actions/using-workflows/workflow-syntax-for-github-actions#permissions

https://docs.github.com/en/actions/using-jobs/assigning-permissions-to-jobs

[Keeping your GitHub Actions and workflows secure Part 1: Preventing pwn requests](https://securitylab.github.com/research/github-actions-preventing-pwn-requests/)

Signed-off-by: nathannaveen <42319948+nathannaveen@users.noreply.github.com>

author: Timvde
message:
Add option for font encoding in the quick start wizard

It is important to set the font encoding next to the input encoding, to
ensure full glyph support. As a default, T1 is chosen, because it's
compatible with utf8, which is the default input encoding.

This fixes #347.

author: alichtman
message:
Display error when a directory is opened (#3090)

When running `$ texstudio DIRECTORY_WITH_TEX_FILES`, the following
error is displayed: "You do not have read permission to the file
$DIRECTORY_WITH_TEX_FILES." This commit makes the error clearer, and
exits texstudio after

Building + Testing:

```bash
$ cd texstudio
$ mkdir build && cd build
$ cmake .. && cmake --build . --parallel && ./texstudio $ARGUMENTS

```

wrapper class to scrartcl.

* [cwl] update tcolorbox.cwl

     \newtcolorbox[init options]{envname}[args][default]{options%keyvals}

   supports multiple keyvals fields in one command in the future,

4. Replace "\name" with "arg".

* [cwl] reduce variants in tcolorbox.cwl

author: muzimuzhi
message:
cwl: mod fontspec, add unicode-math (#1260)

* cwl: add \setromanfont to fontspec.cwl, #1250

\setromanfont is a synonym for \setmainfont.

* cwl: remove first "%keyvals" in fontspec commands

Currently txs accepts at most one "%keyvals" per command/environment.
But some fontspec commands accept two kv-list e.g.,
    \setmainfont[kv-list]{font name}[kv-list]
Since the package manual recommends to always use the second one, the
first "%keyvals" in such commands are deleted.

* cwl: mark some variants as unusual

* cwl: new file "unicode-math.cwl", #1250

author: MeanSquaredError
message:
Fix "Open External Terminal" on Windows (#1096)

* Always keep the program name separately from the program arguments in ExecProgram. Parse the command-line when necessary.
Add support for execution of detached processes in ExecProgram.
Add support for setting native Windows arguments of created processes in ExecProgram.
Use a detatched process when opening an external terminal.
When opening an external terminal on Windows request the creation of a new console.

* Require Qt5.10.0+ for Windows builds.

Co-authored-by: MeanSquaredError <none@none.com>

author: MeanSquaredError
message:
Fix gcc9 compile warnings (#753)

* Silence warnings about dangerous function typecasts inside QtScript headers.

* ws

* Fix a -Wdeprecated-copy warning by GCC9

* Clarify why we need to explicitly define the copy constructor

* Fix whitespace formatting

* Add explicit assignment operators to avoid GCC9 -Wdeprecated-copy warnings

* Add missing comment

* Only disable -Wcast-function-type for QtScript if we are using GCC 8+

* Remove unused labels

* Remove unused variable

* Fix GCC -Wcatch-value by catching exception objects by reference

* Fix GCC -Wimplicit-fallthrough by marking implicit fallthrough with magic comments that are recognized by GCC

* Fix a warning about implicit declaration of vasprintf (on Linux it is declared only if _GNU_SOURCE is defined)

* Silence -Wdeprecated-copy warnings if the compiler is GCC and QT version is between 5.0.0 and 5.12.X

* When building a debug version remove compiler warning flags that are already a part of -Wall and -Wextra

author: MeanSquaredError
message:
Cleanup texstudio.pro (#891)

* Move the list of test classes into a separate project include.

* Remove a code branch for Qt4

* When enabling the test library do not list the required library explicitly. Instead let qmake choose the library file.

* When compiling the project file always display the type of build (debug or release). When tests are turned off in debug builds do not include test classes into the build.

* Move all the qmake checks related to tests into src/tests/tests.pri

* Remove unused qmake project files from quazip

* Move the conditional makefile logic for quazip into src/quazip/quazip/quazip.pri

* Move the conditional makefile logic for hunspell into src/hunspell/hunspell.pri

* -lz and -lshlwapi are used by quazip and internal pdf viewer, so move those library options into their respective places

author: mttnff
message:
Jump to definition of commands/environments (#759)

* Use token to determine position of LinkOverlay

* Add link overlays for command and env (no implementation yet)

* Keep track of definitions of user-defined commands

* Implement jumping to command and environment definitions

* Don't show link overlay for \begin and \end

The current implementation allows to click on the environment
name in \begin{name} to jump to the corresponding definition.
Clicking on \begin does nothing, so it might be misleading
to highlight it with a link overlay.

Alternatively, one could (in the future) provide a link overlay
for the entire \begin{name} expression.

* Improve context menu on environment names

The context menu on \begin{...} displays information
about the enivronment's package. The same information
is now displayed when the context menu is opened on
the environment's name.

* Jump to \usepackage for known commands and environments

* Only pass line handle to addUserCommandDefinition

* Refactor editGotoDefinition and mUserCommandList

Combine mUserCommandGoto and mUserCommandList,
so that the latter also stores names of commands/environments.

Move the lookup of definitions into editGotoDefinition(),
remove/simplify methods editorViewForLabel/Command/... and gotoToLabel/Command/...

* Some fix ups after refactoring

* Add information about the ?p{ext}: file selector in the help section of the config dialog.

* Remove trailing whitespace in C++ source

* Add a test for the ?p{ext}: command-line file selector.

author: IHateYourCode
message:
SmallUsefulFunctions - transformCharacter (#1832)

* Untangled Badge Links

* Description Formatting

* Removed Features (Read the description)

Removed the README feature showcase and made the appeal to visit the website more prevalent.
Considering the website **already** has the exact same showcase **and** the 'Find out more at our website' was pointing the user away from the README in the first place, its sensible to choose one location for the showcase.

* Irrelevant Detail

This detail is already described on texstudio.org but here it is the only instance of a feature point being described in-depth, making it an irregular over-explanation.

* Simplified Heading

* Small Formatting

Indented badges for better separation
and removed (now) duplicate link.

* Moved Contribute Section

to wiki

* Useful Links

Added both downloads as well as releases as the downloads page has more options though the release page is more relevant consider it's on git.

* Link Fix

default relative path would link to /blob/

* Small Formatting Fix

* transformCharacter Rewrite

Rewrote the function to use a lookup, separating the data from the logic and making it overall more readable.
The lookup table uses a char pair to int (charcode) transformation.

static regex where txs has become more flexible.
The folding mechanism/match highlight still is based on qce, so comments
are not handled properly.
This "fix" is a small work-around a probably often occuring nuisance,
but this should be fixed properly sometimes

author: Timvde
message:
Only insert \caption{} once

When using the "Insert Graphic" wizard, if only a short caption is
provided, TeXStudio currently inserts an extra, empty \caption{}.

This happens because inserting a label requires a caption and tries to
add it if the caption is empty. Of course, in the case that only a short
caption is provided, we end up with two \caption{}s.

By checking that both the long and short caption is empty, we make sure
only one caption is inserted.

Initialize m_exitCode to -1 instead of 0

Change the default highlighting colors in dark mode (#1299)

actual character that was highlighted, which may be braces, brackets or
parentheses. This is much easier with a dark background.

* Make braceMatch background brighter

txs-test-qdebug, which was certainly a mishap.

author: sunderme
message:
move highlighting of math,verbatim and picture into syntax checker

This allows for faster load (deferred hightling) and possibly also for
better reactivity especially if math-mode is inverted (e.g. entering $)
Furthermore dynamic highlight handling, i.e. adding math environments
via cwls, seems simpler.

The main bottle neck of the QCE lexer is that every line of text is
checked against tex.qnfa with regexpression. Every added line in
tex.qfna slows down the operation and this obviously scales badly.
